p: GC-MS is a suitable method to analysis the chemical constitute for medicinal herbs extract. Control the conditions will clarify the components. Therefore, in this research used GC-MS method to analysis chemical components of S. monoica Forssk ethanol extracted by MAE. the analysis results revealed about 20 bioactive compounds, as shown in Table 1. The highest peak was detected for compound 2 (Glycine, N,N-Dimethyl-, methyl ester, RT= 6.415 min), followed by compound 11 ( 9,12,15-Octadecatrienoic acid, RT= 24.085 min), compound 9 (n-Hexadecanoic acid, RT= 22.438 min), compound 4 ( N,N-Dimethylglycine, RT=14.906 min), and others according to the NIST library.
